LAGOS – Pastor Lazarus Muoka, General Overseer of The Lord’s Chosen Charismat­ic Revival Ministries, has said that the church’s an­nual crusade ‘What God Has Determined Shall Be Done’, featuring special prayers, will address Ni­geria’s challenges. He said it was import­ant for Nigerians to en­gage in fervent prayers at the beginning of the year to set the tone for the rest of the year. Muoka, said the cru­sade, which usually holds in Mgbidi, Imo State, holds this year in Lagos State, from Thursday 6 to Sun­day, January 9, at the Cho­sen headquarters, Oshodi Apapa Expressway. Jonathan Pays Tribute To Late Olubadan It Will Be Inaccurate For Delta South To Aspire For 2023… The General Overseer, through Pastor Louis Chi­di, Public Relations Offi­cer, stated: “This year’s programme which is the 17th of its kind is special­ly designed to positively change our situation and deal with all enemies of mankind particularly as it relates to our country Nigeria. The programme shall witness rain of prayers that will shatter the shackles of corrup­tion, insecurity, econom­ic and political woes that have become things of concern to our great coun­try.